Proxy
public class EventAliasProxy
extends AliasProxy

An alias representing a group of events.

An event alias is used to give a name of a group events used together in different edges or graphs of a module. This kind of alias can occur in the event alias list of a module, or in the body of a foreach alias construct (ForeachEventAliasProxy). The name of an event can be an arbitrary identifier; it can be indexed to support the use of the foreach alias construct. Its value must be an event list expression (EventListExpressionProxy).

Author:
Robi Malik
